======================================================================
PART 7: Connection to random matrix theory
======================================================================
  Paley adjacency spectrum:
    - Trivial: λ₀ = (p-1)/2 (the Perron eigenvalue)
    - Non-trivial: on circle |λ| = √((p+1)/4)
    - Phases: 2πk/p for k = 1,...,p-1, mapped through χ_p

  This is maximally STRUCTURED — all eigenvalues on one circle.
  Random tournament eigenvalues fill a DISK of radius ~√n/2.
  Paley concentrates all spectral weight on the boundary circle.

  The spectral radius √((p+1)/4) ≈ √p/2 matches the random
  tournament spectral radius of ~√n/2 — same scale, different geometry.

